      <hedline>
        <hl1>Bluestocking Blues</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Dr Helen Feit letter on Judith Shulevitz's September 10 article on Hillary Rodham Clinton holds she would vote for no one who bungled major policy reform or had been investigated for illicit activities (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>According to your article, polls show that white women favor Hillary Clinton's opponent by 5 percentage points. Clinton mishandled health care reform and has been linked to illegal activities involving Whitewater land deals. Could it be that white women are less concerned about sexual politics than Clinton's record? I, for one, would not vote for a man or a woman who had bungled major policy reform or had been investigated for illicit activities.</p>
        <p>Helen Feit, M.D.  Villanova, Pa.</p>
      </block>
